<span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Women's Aid provides a package of vital 24 hour lifeline services through its publications (available in 11 languages including English</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> and running the Freephone 24 Hour National Domestic Violence Helpline in partn</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ership with Refuge</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">0808 2000 247.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Women’s Aid welcomes the opportunity to submit written evidence to the Joint Committee on Human Rights Inquiry into the implications for access to justice of the Government’s proposed legal aid reforms and will restric</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">t comments to our areas of expertise. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We note that Rights of Women have also submitted evidence to this Inquiry and support the whole of their submission. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Legal aid is an essential tool for the protection of women and children from domestic violence. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">enables women to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> secure protection orders, establish safe child contact and access safe accommodation; which in turn can empower women to escape violent relationships. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Women’s Aid </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">has been</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">concerned about impact of legal aid reforms on women experiencing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> domestic violence</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> since the reforms were announced</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. Since </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the introduction of the reforms in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">April 2013 we have received anecdotal evidence from our member services, on our </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">survivors’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> forum and from women themselves that they are experiencing disproportio</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nate difficulties in proving domestic violence in order to access legal aid. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Common complaints include women being denied legal aid because </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">they are not able to produce evidence of domestic violence </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and this leading to women either withdrawing from the cas</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e or representing themselves in court against the perpetrator. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We also have anecdotal evidence from the National Dome</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">stic Violence helpline that they have been receiving an increasing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">number of calls </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">regarding difficulties of women experiencing domestic </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">violence</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> accessing legal aid.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Women’s Aid, Rights of Women and Welsh Women’s Aid are currently collating evidence on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> women’s access to legal aid if they have experienced domestic violence</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. We</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> would be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> happy to share that evidence</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> with the Committee once it is published if it fits within the timeframe of the Inquiry. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In July 2013 the UN Committee on the Elimination of Discrimination Against Women (CEDAW) published their concluding observations of the seventh report of the United </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Kingdom. In its concluding observations the Committee was concerned that the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012, “unduly restricts women’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">access to legal aid</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.” The observations also expressed concern about the conditions applied t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">o accessing legal aid, including </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the proof that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">women </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">had to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">present </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to prove domestic violence. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The CEDAW concluding observations urged the UK to, “a) ensure effective access by women to courts and tribunals, in particular women victims of violence; and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> b) continuously assess the impact of the reforms to legal aid on the protection of women’s rights</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.” </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Women’s Aid supports th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ese</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> recommendation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and calls on the Government to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">implement them without delay. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Women’s Aid believes that the current list of ev</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">idence required from women to prove domestic violence in order to access legal aid does not reflect the reality of women’s experiences. For example, women often do not report violence they experience to the police or health professionals so would have no r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">eports to that effect. Furthermore, spending 24 hours in a refuge is also on the list of evidence required. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Access to refuge accommodation that meets women’s needs can be challenging, particularly in the London area</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Women’s Aid m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ost recent survey of our m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ember</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> services found that in 2011/12, 10,981 women and their children were initially unable to access refuge accommodation because there was not enough space. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">If women are able to access refuge provision they may not necessarily spend a full 24 hours there</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Women’s aid are also concerned about evidence we have heard from women that when they are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> asking General Practitioners to provide evidence of domestic violence to support their claim for legal aid they are being asked to pay </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">around £20 to </span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">£30 for the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">evidence. For women on limited incomes this is a disincentive to collecting the evidence they need</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in order to access legal aid. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Women’s Aid </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">would like to see the domestic violence gateway for legal aid widened with no funding requirement for evidence. W</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e also believe that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">it is vital that women experiencing domestic violence are afforded the adequate levels of legal aid and support that meets their needs and doesn’t undermine their human rights.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> CEDAW, Concluding Observations on the seventh periodic report of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland, July 2013. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Ibid.</span></p></body></html>